	   <tr><td colspan=2>*nod* -- 2x1HS is good when fighting casters, since you can switch out your secondary with a shield, Bash to interrupt, then switch back; time it right and it won't slow down your dual-wielding double-attacking frenzy at all.<br><br>2HS is handy for jousting in PvP, if you're a PvP server or dueling sort -- where nothing but damage matters, since for the most part you'll be running around in circles and even a weighted axe will cycle by the time you swing around and come back.<br><br>So yeah. Keep both maxxed at least, and probably the other three as well, just in case a nice item you weren't expecting drops; otherwise you'll have to miss 50,000 times in a row before your skill catches up to a tolerable level.<br><br>- R<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
